.TH COGFS 4
.SH NAME
cogfs \- cognitive file server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cogfs
[
.B -m
.I mtpt
] [
.B -s
.I srvname
]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I Cogfs
is a file server that exposes Plan9Cog cognitive computing operations
via the 9P protocol. It provides a file-based interface to the AtomSpace,
PLN inference engine, and ECAN attention allocation network.
.PP
The
.B -m
option specifies the mount point (default:
.BR /mnt/cog ).
.PP
The
.B -s
option specifies a service name for
.IR srv (3)
(default: none).
.PP
The file tree contains:
.TF ecanctl
.TP
.B atoms
Lists all atoms in the AtomSpace. Read-only.
.TP
.B atomctl
Control file for atom operations. Write commands to create, delete, or modify atoms.
.TP
.B pln
Shows PLN inference results. Read-only.
.TP
.B plnctl
Control file for PLN inference. Write queries to perform inference.
.TP
.B ecan
Shows ECAN state including attention allocation. Read-only.
.TP
.B ecanctl
Control file for ECAN operations. Write commands to allocate or spread attention.
.TP
.B pattern
Pattern matching results. Read-only.
.TP
.B stats
System statistics including atom count, memory usage, and uptime. Read-only.
.TP
.B ctl
General control file for system operations.
.SH EXAMPLES
Start the cognitive file server:
.IP
.EX
cogfs -m /mnt/cog
.EE
.PP
List atoms:
.IP
.EX
cat /mnt/cog/atoms
.EE
.PP
Create an atom:
.IP
.EX
echo 'create 1 concept:cat' > /mnt/cog/atomctl
.EE
.PP
Show system statistics:
.IP
.EX
cat /mnt/cog/stats
.EE
.SH FILES
.TF /sys/include/plan9cog.h
.TP
.B /mnt/cog
Default mount point
.TP
.B /sys/include/plan9cog.h
Plan9Cog main header
.SH SOURCE
.B /sys/src/cmd/cogfs
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR cogctl (1),
.IR cogdemo (1),
.IR plan9cog (2),
.IR 9p (2)
.SH BUGS
The file server is single-threaded and may block on long operations.
Pattern matching not yet exposed via files.
